						<label.name>&#167; </label.name>
						<label.designator>1:16.</label.designator>
						<headtext>Applicability of Federal Truth in Lending Act, Real Estate Settlement Procedures Act, and Interstate Land Sales Full Disclosure Act</headtext>
					</head>
				</doc.title>
			</section.front>
			<section.body>
					<para>
						<paratext>The taxpayer is conducting a business and the ordinary and reasonable expenses of the business are deductible against income realized from the operation.</paratext>
					</para>
					<?pagebreak label="24"?>
					<para>
						<paratext>The second category of real estate is property used as a personal residence. This is technically a capital asset, which is the next category to be discussed.</paratext>
					</para>
					<?pagebreak label="25"?>
					<para>
						<paratext>Being a personal residence, however, causes different tax doctrines to apply. Gain on the sale of a residence held for longer than one year is taxed as long-term capital gain.</paratext>
					</para>
			</section.body>
